29bool DetectSaturation(rtc::ArrayView<const float> y) {
30 for (auto y_k : y) {
31 if (y_k >= 32700.0f || y_k <= -32700.0f) {
32 return true;
33 }
34 }
35 return false;
36}

38// Retrieves a value from a field trial if it is available. If no value is
39// present, the default value is returned. If the retrieved value is beyond the
40// specified limits, the default value is returned instead.
41void RetrieveFieldTrialValue(const char* trial_name,
42 float min,
43 float max,
44 float* value_to_update) {
45 const std::string field_trial_str = field_trial::FindFullName(trial_name);
46
47 FieldTrialParameter<double> field_trial_param(/*key=*/"", *value_to_update);
48
49 ParseFieldTrial({&field_trial_param}, field_trial_str);
50 float field_trial_value = static_cast<float>(field_trial_param.Get());
51
52 if (field_trial_value >= min && field_trial_value <= max) {
53 *value_to_update = field_trial_value;
54 }
55}
56
57void RetrieveFieldTrialValue(const char* trial_name,
58 int min,
59 int max,
60 int* value_to_update) {
61 const std::string field_trial_str = field_trial::FindFullName(trial_name);
62
63 FieldTrialParameter<int> field_trial_param(/*key=*/"", *value_to_update);
64
65 ParseFieldTrial({&field_trial_param}, field_trial_str);
66 float field_trial_value = field_trial_param.Get();
67
68 if (field_trial_value >= min && field_trial_value <= max) {
69 *value_to_update = field_trial_value;
70 }
71}

73void FillSubFrameView(
74 AudioBuffer* frame,
75 size_t sub_frame_index,
76 std::vector<std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<float>>>* sub_frame_view) {
77 RTC_DCHECK_GE(1, sub_frame_index);
78 RTC_DCHECK_LE(0, sub_frame_index);
79 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame->num_bands(), sub_frame_view->size());
80 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame->num_channels(), (*sub_frame_view)[0].size());
81 for (size_t band = 0; band < sub_frame_view->size(); ++band) {
82 for (size_t channel = 0; channel < (*sub_frame_view)[0].size(); ++channel) {
83 (*sub_frame_view)[band][channel] = rtc::ArrayView<float>(
84 &frame->split_bands(channel)[band][sub_frame_index * kSubFrameLength],
85 kSubFrameLength);
86 }
87 }
88}
89
90void FillSubFrameView(
91 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* frame,
92 size_t sub_frame_index,
93 std::vector<std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<float>>>* sub_frame_view) {
94 RTC_DCHECK_GE(1, sub_frame_index);
95 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame->size(), sub_frame_view->size());
96 RTC_DCHECK_EQ((*frame)[0].size(), (*sub_frame_view)[0].size());
97 for (size_t band = 0; band < frame->size(); ++band) {
98 for (size_t channel = 0; channel < (*frame)[band].size(); ++channel) {
99 (*sub_frame_view)[band][channel] = rtc::ArrayView<float>(
100 &(*frame)[band][channel][sub_frame_index * kSubFrameLength],
101 kSubFrameLength);
102 }
103 }
104}

106void ProcessCaptureFrameContent(
107 AudioBuffer* linear_output,
108 AudioBuffer* capture,
109 bool level_change,
110 bool saturated_microphone_signal,
111 size_t sub_frame_index,
112 FrameBlocker* capture_blocker,
113 BlockFramer* linear_output_framer,
114 BlockFramer* output_framer,
115 BlockProcessor* block_processor,
116 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* linear_output_block,
117 std::vector<std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<float>>>*
118 linear_output_sub_frame_view,
119 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* capture_block,
120 std::vector<std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<float>>>* capture_sub_frame_view) {
121 FillSubFrameView(capture, sub_frame_index, capture_sub_frame_view);
122
123 if (linear_output) {
124 RTC_DCHECK(linear_output_framer);
125 RTC_DCHECK(linear_output_block);
126 RTC_DCHECK(linear_output_sub_frame_view);
127 FillSubFrameView(linear_output, sub_frame_index,
128 linear_output_sub_frame_view);
129 }
130
131 capture_blocker->InsertSubFrameAndExtractBlock(*capture_sub_frame_view,
132 capture_block);
133 block_processor->ProcessCapture(level_change, saturated_microphone_signal,
134 linear_output_block, capture_block);
135 output_framer->InsertBlockAndExtractSubFrame(*capture_block,
136 capture_sub_frame_view);
137
138 if (linear_output) {
139 RTC_DCHECK(linear_output_framer);
140 linear_output_framer->InsertBlockAndExtractSubFrame(
141 *linear_output_block, linear_output_sub_frame_view);
142 }
143}
144
145void ProcessRemainingCaptureFrameContent(
146 bool level_change,
147 bool saturated_microphone_signal,
148 FrameBlocker* capture_blocker,
149 BlockFramer* linear_output_framer,
150 BlockFramer* output_framer,
151 BlockProcessor* block_processor,
152 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* linear_output_block,
153 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* block) {
154 if (!capture_blocker->IsBlockAvailable()) {
155 return;
156 }
157
158 capture_blocker->ExtractBlock(block);
159 block_processor->ProcessCapture(level_change, saturated_microphone_signal,
160 linear_output_block, block);
161 output_framer->InsertBlock(*block);
162
163 if (linear_output_framer) {
164 RTC_DCHECK(linear_output_block);
165 linear_output_framer->InsertBlock(*linear_output_block);
166 }
167}
168
169void BufferRenderFrameContent(
170 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* render_frame,
171 size_t sub_frame_index,
172 FrameBlocker* render_blocker,
173 BlockProcessor* block_processor,
174 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* block,
175 std::vector<std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<float>>>* sub_frame_view) {
176 FillSubFrameView(render_frame, sub_frame_index, sub_frame_view);
177 render_blocker->InsertSubFrameAndExtractBlock(*sub_frame_view, block);
178 block_processor->BufferRender(*block);
179}
180
181void BufferRemainingRenderFrameContent(
182 FrameBlocker* render_blocker,
183 BlockProcessor* block_processor,
184 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* block) {
185 if (!render_blocker->IsBlockAvailable()) {
186 return;
187 }
188 render_blocker->ExtractBlock(block);
189 block_processor->BufferRender(*block);
190}
191
192void CopyBufferIntoFrame(const AudioBuffer& buffer,
193 size_t num_bands,
194 size_t num_channels,
195 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* frame) {
196 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_bands, frame->size());
197 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_channels, (*frame)[0].size());
198 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize, (*frame)[0][0].size());
199 for (size_t band = 0; band < num_bands; ++band) {
200 for (size_t channel = 0; channel < num_channels; ++channel) {
201 rtc::ArrayView<const float> buffer_view(
202 &buffer.split_bands_const(channel)[band][0],
203 AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize);
204 std::copy(buffer_view.begin(), buffer_view.end(),
205 (*frame)[band][channel].begin());
206 }
207 }
208}

512 // Field trial-based overrides of individual suppressor parameters.
513 RetrieveFieldTrialValue(
514 "WebRTC-Aec3SuppressorNearendLfMaskTransparentOverride", 0.f, 10.f,

584class EchoCanceller3::RenderWriter {
585 public:
586 RenderWriter(ApmDataDumper* data_dumper,
587 const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
588 SwapQueue<std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>,
589 Aec3RenderQueueItemVerifier>* render_transfer_queue,
590 size_t num_bands,
591 size_t num_channels);
592
593 RenderWriter() = delete;
594 RenderWriter(const RenderWriter&) = delete;
595 RenderWriter& operator=(const RenderWriter&) = delete;
596
597 ~RenderWriter();
598 void Insert(const AudioBuffer& input);
599
600 private:
601 ApmDataDumper* data_dumper_;
602 const size_t num_bands_;
603 const size_t num_channels_;
604 std::unique_ptr<HighPassFilter> high_pass_filter_;
605 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>> render_queue_input_frame_;
606 SwapQueue<std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>,
607 Aec3RenderQueueItemVerifier>* render_transfer_queue_;
608};
609
610EchoCanceller3::RenderWriter::RenderWriter(
611 ApmDataDumper* data_dumper,
612 const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
613 SwapQueue<std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>,
614 Aec3RenderQueueItemVerifier>* render_transfer_queue,
615 size_t num_bands,
616 size_t num_channels)
617 : data_dumper_(data_dumper),
618 num_bands_(num_bands),
619 num_channels_(num_channels),
620 render_queue_input_frame_(
621 num_bands_,
622 std::vector<std::vector<float>>(
623 num_channels_,
624 std::vector<float>(AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize, 0.f))),
625 render_transfer_queue_(render_transfer_queue) {
626 RTC_DCHECK(data_dumper);
627 if (config.filter.high_pass_filter_echo_reference) {
628 high_pass_filter_ = std::make_unique<HighPassFilter>(16000, num_channels);
629 }
630}
631
632EchoCanceller3::RenderWriter::~RenderWriter() = default;
633
634void EchoCanceller3::RenderWriter::Insert(const AudioBuffer& input) {
635 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize, input.num_frames_per_band());
636 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_bands_, input.num_bands());
637 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_channels_, input.num_channels());
638
639 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/8759) Temporary work-around.
640 if (num_bands_ != input.num_bands())
641 return;
642
643 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_render_input", AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize,
644 &input.split_bands_const(0)[0][0], 16000, 1);
645
646 CopyBufferIntoFrame(input, num_bands_, num_channels_,
647 &render_queue_input_frame_);
648 if (high_pass_filter_) {
649 high_pass_filter_->Process(&render_queue_input_frame_[0]);
650 }
651
652 static_cast<void>(render_transfer_queue_->Insert(&render_queue_input_frame_));
653}
654
655int EchoCanceller3::instance_count_ = 0;
656
657EchoCanceller3::EchoCanceller3(const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
658 int sample_rate_hz,
659 size_t num_render_channels,
660 size_t num_capture_channels)
661 : EchoCanceller3(AdjustConfig(config),
662 sample_rate_hz,
663 num_render_channels,
664 num_capture_channels,
665 std::unique_ptr<BlockProcessor>(
666 BlockProcessor::Create(AdjustConfig(config),
667 sample_rate_hz,
668 num_render_channels,
669 num_capture_channels))) {}
670EchoCanceller3::EchoCanceller3(const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
671 int sample_rate_hz,
672 size_t num_render_channels,
673 size_t num_capture_channels,
674 std::unique_ptr<BlockProcessor> block_processor)
675 : data_dumper_(
676 new ApmDataDumper(rtc::AtomicOps::Increment(&instance_count_))),
677 config_(config),
678 sample_rate_hz_(sample_rate_hz),
679 num_bands_(NumBandsForRate(sample_rate_hz_)),
680 num_render_channels_(num_render_channels),
681 num_capture_channels_(num_capture_channels),
682 output_framer_(num_bands_, num_capture_channels_),
683 capture_blocker_(num_bands_, num_capture_channels_),
684 render_blocker_(num_bands_, num_render_channels_),
685 render_transfer_queue_(
686 kRenderTransferQueueSizeFrames,
687 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>(
688 num_bands_,
689 std::vector<std::vector<float>>(
690 num_render_channels_,
691 std::vector<float>(AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize, 0.f))),
692 Aec3RenderQueueItemVerifier(num_bands_,
693 num_render_channels_,
694 AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize)),
695 block_processor_(std::move(block_processor)),
696 render_queue_output_frame_(
697 num_bands_,
698 std::vector<std::vector<float>>(
699 num_render_channels_,
700 std::vector<float>(AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize, 0.f))),
701 render_block_(
702 num_bands_,
703 std::vector<std::vector<float>>(num_render_channels_,
704 std::vector<float>(kBlockSize, 0.f))),
705 capture_block_(
706 num_bands_,
707 std::vector<std::vector<float>>(num_capture_channels_,
708 std::vector<float>(kBlockSize, 0.f))),
709 render_sub_frame_view_(
710 num_bands_,
711 std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<float>>(num_render_channels_)),
712 capture_sub_frame_view_(
713 num_bands_,
714 std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<float>>(num_capture_channels_)) {
715 RTC_DCHECK(ValidFullBandRate(sample_rate_hz_));
716
717 if (config_.delay.fixed_capture_delay_samples > 0) {
718 block_delay_buffer_.reset(new BlockDelayBuffer(
719 num_capture_channels_, num_bands_, AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize,
720 config_.delay.fixed_capture_delay_samples));
721 }
722
723 render_writer_.reset(new RenderWriter(data_dumper_.get(), config_,
724 &render_transfer_queue_, num_bands_,
725 num_render_channels_));
726
727 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_bands_, std::max(sample_rate_hz_, 16000) / 16000);
728 RTC_DCHECK_GE(kMaxNumBands, num_bands_);
729
730 if (config_.filter.export_linear_aec_output) {
731 linear_output_framer_.reset(new BlockFramer(1, num_capture_channels_));
732 linear_output_block_ =
733 std::make_unique<std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>>(
734 1, std::vector<std::vector<float>>(
735 num_capture_channels_, std::vector<float>(kBlockSize, 0.f)));
736 linear_output_sub_frame_view_ =
737 std::vector<std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<float>>>(
738 1, std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<float>>(num_capture_channels_));
739 }
740}

742EchoCanceller3::~EchoCanceller3() = default;

744void EchoCanceller3::AnalyzeRender(const AudioBuffer& render) {
745 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&render_race_checker_);
746
747 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(render.num_channels(), num_render_channels_);
748 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_call_order",
749 static_cast<int>(EchoCanceller3ApiCall::kRender));
750
751 return render_writer_->Insert(render);
752}
753
754void EchoCanceller3::AnalyzeCapture(const AudioBuffer& capture) {
755 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&capture_race_checker_);
756 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_capture_analyze_input", capture.num_frames(),
757 capture.channels_const()[0], sample_rate_hz_, 1);
758 saturated_microphone_signal_ = false;
759 for (size_t channel = 0; channel < capture.num_channels(); ++channel) {
760 saturated_microphone_signal_ |=
761 DetectSaturation(rtc::ArrayView<const float>(
762 capture.channels_const()[channel], capture.num_frames()));
763 if (saturated_microphone_signal_) {
764 break;
765 }
766 }
767}
768
769void EchoCanceller3::ProcessCapture(AudioBuffer* capture, bool level_change) {
770 ProcessCapture(capture, nullptr, level_change);
771}
772
773void EchoCanceller3::ProcessCapture(AudioBuffer* capture,
774 AudioBuffer* linear_output,
775 bool level_change) {
776 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&capture_race_checker_);
777 RTC_DCHECK(capture);
778 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_bands_, capture->num_bands());
779 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize, capture->num_frames_per_band());
780 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(capture->num_channels(), num_capture_channels_);
781 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_call_order",
782 static_cast<int>(EchoCanceller3ApiCall::kCapture));
783
784 if (linear_output && !linear_output_framer_) {
785 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Trying to retrieve the linear AEC output without "
786 "properly configuring AEC3.";
787 RTC_NOTREACHED();
788 }
789
790 // Report capture call in the metrics and periodically update API call
791 // metrics.
792 api_call_metrics_.ReportCaptureCall();
793
794 // Optionally delay the capture signal.
795 if (config_.delay.fixed_capture_delay_samples > 0) {
796 RTC_DCHECK(block_delay_buffer_);
797 block_delay_buffer_->DelaySignal(capture);
798 }
799
800 rtc::ArrayView<float> capture_lower_band = rtc::ArrayView<float>(
801 &capture->split_bands(0)[0][0], AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize);
802
803 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_capture_input", capture_lower_band, 16000, 1);
804
805 EmptyRenderQueue();
806
807 ProcessCaptureFrameContent(linear_output, capture, level_change,
808 saturated_microphone_signal_, 0, &capture_blocker_,
809 linear_output_framer_.get(), &output_framer_,
810 block_processor_.get(), linear_output_block_.get(),
811 &linear_output_sub_frame_view_, &capture_block_,
812 &capture_sub_frame_view_);
813
814 ProcessCaptureFrameContent(linear_output, capture, level_change,
815 saturated_microphone_signal_, 1, &capture_blocker_,
816 linear_output_framer_.get(), &output_framer_,
817 block_processor_.get(), linear_output_block_.get(),
818 &linear_output_sub_frame_view_, &capture_block_,
819 &capture_sub_frame_view_);
820
821 ProcessRemainingCaptureFrameContent(
822 level_change, saturated_microphone_signal_, &capture_blocker_,
823 linear_output_framer_.get(), &output_framer_, block_processor_.get(),
824 linear_output_block_.get(), &capture_block_);
825
826 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_capture_output", AudioBuffer::kSplitBandSize,
827 &capture->split_bands(0)[0][0], 16000, 1);
828}

850
851EchoCanceller3Config EchoCanceller3::CreateDefaultConfig(
852 size_t num_render_channels,
853 size_t num_capture_channels) {
854 EchoCanceller3Config cfg;
855 if (num_render_channels > 1) {
856 // Use shorter and more rapidly adapting coarse filter to compensate for
857 // thge increased number of total filter parameters to adapt.
858 cfg.filter.coarse.length_blocks = 11;
859 cfg.filter.coarse.rate = 0.95f;
860 cfg.filter.coarse_initial.length_blocks = 11;
861 cfg.filter.coarse_initial.rate = 0.95f;
862
863 // Use more concervative suppressor behavior for non-nearend speech.
864 cfg.suppressor.normal_tuning.max_dec_factor_lf = 0.35f;
865 cfg.suppressor.normal_tuning.max_inc_factor = 1.5f;
866 }
867 return cfg;
868}
869
870void EchoCanceller3::EmptyRenderQueue() {
871 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&capture_race_checker_);
872 bool frame_to_buffer =
873 render_transfer_queue_.Remove(&render_queue_output_frame_);
874 while (frame_to_buffer) {
875 // Report render call in the metrics.
876 api_call_metrics_.ReportRenderCall();
877
878 BufferRenderFrameContent(&render_queue_output_frame_, 0, &render_blocker_,
879 block_processor_.get(), &render_block_,
880 &render_sub_frame_view_);
881
882 BufferRenderFrameContent(&render_queue_output_frame_, 1, &render_blocker_,
883 block_processor_.get(), &render_block_,
884 &render_sub_frame_view_);
885
886 BufferRemainingRenderFrameContent(&render_blocker_, block_processor_.get(),
887 &render_block_);
888
889 frame_to_buffer =
890 render_transfer_queue_.Remove(&render_queue_output_frame_);
891 }
